data.title: Where DC Meets
data.meta_description: The Wharf is DC's most exciting waterfront neighborhood. It is home to over 80 restaurants and shops, four hotels, and thousands of residents and workers.
data.text:
Visit Camp Wharf

It's S'more fun at The Wharf! This season, visit Camp Wharf where you'll find a wood-burning fire and a vintage Airstream trailer with everything you need for the perfect s'moreâ€”marshmallows, chocolate, graham crackers, and roasting sticks. Guests can also donate to WAFF - the Washington Area Fuel Fund to help their neighbors in need meet their energy bill.

S'mores & more

Catch a Concert

Get your friends and family together for a concert at one of our fantastic concert venues. Catch a mega show at The Anthem or intimate performance at Union Stage and Pearl Street Warehouse. From country and rock to indie and pop, our venues featuring a variety of music genres throughout the year.

Music Venues at The Wharf

Rent a Boat

Whether you want to rent a kayak, paddleboard, electric boat, or pontoon boat, The Wharf has you covered. Explore our captained and self-operated power boats, boat rental clubs, and sightseeing cruises. Grab food and drinks from a Wharf restaurant and make it a picnic on the water!
